DockingModule.name: Docking Module
DockingModule.Description:
The Docking Module allows the user to create a fixed
 Docking Zone. This Zone can then be Docked/Undocked
 with by using the Ship Core's built-in Docking Beam.
 
 Docking Modules can be orientated, and must not have
 any obstructions in their Zone (The Green Square), other
 than the Docked Item in question.
 
 Otherwise, the Module will go offline, and no Docking
 will be allowed until the obstruction is removed.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

DockingEnhancer.name: Docking Enhancer
DockingEnhancer.Description:
The Docking Enhancer can be used to increase the
 size of the Docking Zone created by a Docking Module.
 
 To use them, you must simply connect them to the
 Docking Module whose zone you want to increase by
 selecting the Module with C, and then using V to
 connect each Enhancer. As with Weapons, and other
 blocks that can be connected. The Docking Enhancers
 do not have to be adjacent to the Docking Module.
 
 Alternatively, you can lay a Docking Module down,
 select it with C, and then each Docking Enhancer you
 put down afterwards will be automatically connected to
 the Docking Module.
 
 As of now, there is no need to orientate Docking
 Enhancers, as they will increase the Docking Zone all
 around, no matter which way they are facing, or where
 they are put in correlation to the Docking Module.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

TurretDockingUnit.name: Turret Docking Unit
TurretDockingUnit.Description:
The Turret Docking Unit functions very similarly to the
 Docking Module. Except that it allows the Docked Item
 to freely rotate, thus enabling Turret capabilites.
 
 All the other rules and limitations of the Docking Module
 still apply. You can orientate the block and thus the Zone,
 and there must be no other blocks than the Docked Item
 in the zone.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

TurretDockingEnhancerUnit.name: Turret Docking Enhancer Unit
TurretDockingEnhancerUnit.Description:
The Turret Docking Enhancer Unit can be used for the
 Turret Docking Unit, much like the Docking Enhancer
 can be for the Docking Module.
 
 To use them, you must simply connect them to the
 Turret Docking Unit whose zone you want to increase
 by selecting the Unit with C, and then using V to
 connect each Enhancer. As with Weapons, and other
 blocks that can be connected. The Turret Docking
 Enhancer Units do not have to be adjacent to the
 Turret Docking Unit.
 
 Alternatively, you can lay a Turret Docking Unit down,
 select it with C, and then each Turret Docking
 Enhancer Unit you put down afterwards will be
 automatically connected to the Turret Docking Unit.
 
 As of now, there is no need to orientate Turret Docking
 Enhancer Unit, as they will increase the Docking Zone
 all around, no matter which way they are facing, or
 where they are put in correlation to the Turret Docking
 Unit.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

GravityUnit.name: Gravity Unit
GravityUnit.Description:
The Gravity Unit, once placed and activated, can be used
 to simulate a simple field of Gravity.
 
 Press $ACTIVATE to Activate/Deactivate.
 
 Most common uses include on the interiors of
 Ships and Space Stations.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

BuildBlock.name: Build Block
BuildBlock.Description:
The Build Block can be placed almost anywhere, and
 allows the user to enter Build Mode without the need of
 a Ship or Ship Core. Enabling Structures other than ships
 to be built.
 
 Press $ACTIVATE to get in or out of the Build Block.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

PlexStorage.name: PlexStorage
PlexStorage.Description:
The PlexStorage functions like a persistent, static
 inventory. Enabling the user to store items from their
 inventory in it. The current capactity is a 7x5 Grid (Same
 as your inventory).
 
 Press $ACTIVATE to Open/Close.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

PlexDoor.name: PlexDoor
PlexDoor.Description:
The PlexDoor can used to create a Wall or Floor than
 can be open or closed.
 
 Multiple adjacent blocks register as one door. Meaing
 activating one will activate all PlexDoors touching it.
 Useful for creating large doors.
 
 Press $ACTIVATE to Open/Close.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

SDHCTxmPower.name: SD HCT xm3.4 Power
SDHCTxmPower.Description:
The SD HCT xm3.4 Power provides a technically
 infinite source of power for all things requiring it. It's
 only limitations being:
 
 Power Load (Total Power Storage)
 Power Recharge Rate (e/sec)
 
 Grouping SD HCT xm3.4 Power together has the
 following benefits:
 
 Dimension of the group = Recharge Increase (e/sec)
 Count of modules in group = Power Load (Total Power)
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

FactionModule.name: Faction Module
FactionModule.Description:
The Faction Module can add ownership to Ships,
 Space Stations, Planets, and Asteroids.
 
 It is able to withstand some punishment, but can be
 destroyed. So it should be well protected.
 
 Ships fitted with a Faction Module cannot be destroyed
 in their Faction's home base, as long as it's landed or
 fix-docked.
 
 Only one Faction Module can be placed per structure.
 
 The Faction Module allows several features for its user.
 Press $ACTIVATE on it to gain access to them.
 
 These features include:
 - Password Protection
 - Permissions: Single User/Faction/All
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

FactionHub.name: Faction Hub
FactionHub.Description:
This module contains an interface
 for factions. Users can look up
 lists, join recruting factions,
 and see the overall
 relationshp of factions to
 each other.
 
 A permanent faction hub can be found on every shop.

SDpcPowerTank.name: SD pc1.3 Power Tank
SDpcPowerTank.Description:
This module stores power,
 and increases the max power capacity.
 
 For power generation, please buy
 the SD HCT xm3.4 Power

HANGINGLIGHTYELLOW.Description: This is a yellow light, hanging from a cable.

ShipCore.name: Ship Core
ShipCore.Description:
The Ship Core is the most basic part in Ship Building.
 You need at least one to begin building a ship.
 
 To place a Ship Core in open space, simply press X
 with it selected in your Hotbar.

WeaponsComputer.name: Weapons Computer
WeaponsComputer.Description:
The Weapons Computer is required for creating
 functioning AntiMatter Cannon systems.
 
 It is capable of controlling a technically infinite amount
 of Cannons. Once placed, you can select/deselect it
 with C, and link Cannons using V while it is selected
 and you are looking at an AntiMatter Cannon.
 Press $ACTIVATE to get in/out of the Computer.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

AntiMatterCannon.name: AntiMatter Cannon
AntiMatterCannon.Description:
The AntiMatter Cannon, when used in conjunction with
 a Weapons Computer, can create a basic but effective
 weapons system. 
 
 The AntiMatter Cannon fires a beam-like projectile in a 
 straight line.
 
 AntiMatter Cannons do benefit from being grouped
 together (Being Adjacent to one another), enabling the
 Cannons to fire further, fly faster, hit harder, and reload
 more efficiently. You can also choose which AntiMatter
 Cannon outputs the projectile by going into Astronaut
 Mode, finding the Cannon Block you want to output the
 beam, and pressing $ACTIVATE on it.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

SalvageComputer.name: Salvage Computer
SalvageComputer.Description:
The Salvage Computer is required for creating
 functioning Salvage Cannon systems.
 
 It is capable of controlling a technically infinite amount
 of Cannons. Once placed, you can select/deselect it
 with C, and link Cannons using V while it is selected
 and you are looking at a Salvage Cannon.
 Press $ACTIVATE to get in/out of the Computer.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

SalvageCannon.name: Salvage Cannon
SalvageCannon.Description:
The Salvage Cannon, when used in conjunction with
 a Salvage Computer, can create an effective
 salvage system. 
 
 The Salvage Cannon fires a laser-like projectile in a 
 straight line.
 
 Salvage Cannons do benefit from being grouped
 together (Being Adjacent to one another), enabling the
 Cannons to salvage faster.
 
 Salvage Cannons can be used to Salvage parts from
 inactive Ships and Stations or mine Asteroids and
 Planets for resources.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

AstroTechnician.name: AstroTechnician
AstroTechnician.Description:
The AstroTechnician is required for creating
 functioning AstroTechnobeam systems.
 
 It is capable of controlling a technically infinite amount
 of Technobeams. Once placed, you can select/deselect it
 with C, and link Technobeams using V while it is selected
 and you are looking at a Technobeam.
 Press $ACTIVATE to get in/out of the AstroTechnician.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

AstroTechnobeam.name: AstroTechnobeam
AstroTechnobeam.Description:
The AstroTechnobeam, when used in conjunction with
 a AstroTechnician, can create an effective repair
 system. 
 
 The fires AstroTechnobeam a laser-like projectile in a 
 straight line.
 
 AstroTechnobeams do benefit from being grouped
 together (Being Adjacent to one another), enabling the
 Technobeams to repair faster.
 
 AstroTechnobeams can used to repair damage to
 blocks.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

dMissileCPU.name: d1000 Missile CPU
dMissileCPU.Description:
The d1000 Missile CPU is required for creating
 functioning d1000 Missile Array systems.
 
 As it lacks the circuitry, the d1000 Missile CPU can only
 dumb-fire (Meaning no target lock or tracking) its
 connected Arrays.
 
 It is capable of controlling a technically infinite amount
 of d1000 Missile Arrays. Once placed, you can select
 /deselect it with C, and link Arrays using V while it is
 selected and you are looking at an Array.
 Press $ACTIVATE to get in/out of the CPU.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

dMissileArray.name: d1000 Missile Array
dMissileArray.Description:
The d1000 Missile Array, when used in conjunction with
 a d1000 Missile CPU, can create a basic but effective
 missile system. 
 
 The d1000 Missile Array fires a missile with a straight
 flight path. As they lack the circuitry, the d1000 Missile
 Arrays cannot track or lock targets, meaning they are
 mainly meant for stationary targets or demolition.
 
 d1000 Missile Arrays do benefit from being grouped
 together (Being Adjacent to one another), enabling the
 Arrays to fire further, fly faster, hit harder, reload more
 efficiently, and pack a bigger splash radius.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

SDKBMissileCPU.name: SD KB Missile CPU
SDKBMissileCPU.Description:
The SD KB Missile CPU is required for creating
 functioning SD KB Missile Array systems.
 
 The SD KB Missile CPU comes equipped with more
 advanced computing technology, enabling its Arrays to
 Heatseeking capabilites. It will self lock (Meaning the
 target you may have selected/intended might not
 matter) to the nearest ship, disregarding your own of
 course. Meaning that you should fire with care around
 friendly ships, as it will change targets if intercepted by
 a closer heat signature.
 
 It is capable of controlling a technically infinite amount
 of SD KB Missile Arrays. Once placed, you can select
 /deselect it with C, and link Arrays using V while it is
 selected and you are looking at an Array.
 Press $ACTIVATE to get in/out of the CPU.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

SDKBMissileArray.name: SD KB Missile Array
SDKBMissileArray.Description:
The SD KB Missile Array, when used in conjunction
 with a SD KB Missile CPU, can create an effective
 missile system. 
 
 The SD KB Missile Array fires a missile with an initial
 straight flight path, until it finds the nearest heat
 signature. Then it will procede to track that target, until
 it hits it, finds a closer heat signature, or runs out of fuel
 They still lack the circuitry for manual target locking.
 
 SD KB Missile Arrays do benefit from being grouped
 together (Being Adjacent to one another), enabling the
 Arrays to fire further, fly faster, hit harder, reload more
 efficiently, and pack a bigger splash radius.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

SDBBMissileComputer.name: SD-BB Missile Computer
SDBBMissileComputer.Description:
The SD-BB Missile CPU is required for creating
 functioning SD-BB Missile Array systems.
 
 The SD-BB Missile CPU comes equipped with the top
 tier oc computing technology, enabling its Arrays to
 to detect all Uncloaked/Unjammed targets in its sector.
 It also has the ability to lock targets, and will stay on
 that target. To lock targets, keep your crosshair on them
 , until the circle turns green, and fire when ready.
 
 It is capable of controlling a technically infinite amount
 of SD-BB Missile Arrays. Once placed, you can select
 /deselect it with C, and link Arrays using V while it is
 selected and you are looking at an Array.
 Press $ACTIVATE to get in/out of the CPU.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP
SDBBMissileComputer.FullName: SchemaDyne BLOCKADE BUSTER PREMIUM missile Computer

SDBBMissileArray.name: SD-BB Missile Array
SDBBMissileArray.Description:
The SD-BB Missile Array, when used in conjunction
 with a SD-BB Missile CPU, can create an effective
 missile system. 
 
 The SD-BB Missile Array fires a missile with an initial
 straight flight path, unless it has a preset target locked.
 In which case it will course correct to ensure it hits its
 target.
 
 SD-BB Missile Arrays do benefit from being grouped
 together (Being Adjacent to one another), enabling the
 Arrays to fire further, fly faster, hit harder, reload more
 efficiently, and pack a bigger splash radius.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP
SDBBMissileArray.FullName: SchemaDyne BLOCKADE BUSTER PREMIUM missile array

DisIntegraterExplosive.name: Dis-Integrater (Explosive)
DisIntegraterExplosive.Description:
The Dis-Integrater is a crude, but effective explosive.
 It can be chained with other Dis-Integrater blocks to
 increase the splash and damage created. As of now,
 they are mainly activated by means of collisions with any
 block, and will explode on contact. Making an effective
 means for creating bombs, mines, and battering rams.
 The applications are limited only by the user's creativity.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP
DisIntegraterExplosive.FullName: R0GUE MultiMatter subAtomic Particle disintegration unit

CCloaker.name: 0C Cloaker
CCloaker.Description:
The 0C Cloaker is capable of rendering an object
 completely invisible for a period of time before needing
 to reset. It's limitations rely on the number of 0Cs
 aboard the object, and the dimension of its grouping.
 
 Meaning larger objects will need a larger dimensioned
 group of 0C Cloakers.
 
 To use, you must assign them to a key like other ship
 systems.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

xRadarJammer.name: 10x RadarJammer
xRadarJammer.Description:
The 10x RadarJammer will hide your Signature to all
 other pilots in the sector. However it's limitations are
 similar to that of the 0C Cloaker. The higher the number
 and the larger of the dimension of 10x RadarJammers
 aboard the ship will create more reliable jamming.
 
 To use, you must assign them to a key like other ship
 systems.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

HyperfluxCoilThruster.name: Hyperflux Coil Thruster
HyperfluxCoilThruster.Description:
The Hyperflux Coil Thruster is capable of providing
 propulsion for ships of all shapes and sizes. Their main
 fuel source is power, provided by the SD HCT xm3.4
 Power block.
 
 They do benefit from being groups, enabling more thrust,
 quicker acceleration, and better handling. All that the cost
 of increased power requirements.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

SDShieldDisperser.name: SD Shield Disperser
SDShieldDisperser.Description:
The SD Shield Disperser is capable of generating a
 shield around the object it is attached to.
 
 While it is not affected by the tradition (Adjacent)
 grouping mechanism, they are affected by the
 non-traditional (Non-adjacent) grouping mechanism.
 Meaning that two SD Shield Dispersers next to each
 other, and two that are apart but attached to the same
 object, will have the same output.
 
 The following advantages/disadvantages can be found
 when placing more than one SD Shield Disperser:
 
 Shield Load (Total Damage Absorbed)
 Shield Recharge Rate (e/sec)
 Shield Power Usage (e/sec)
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

SDCockpit.name: SD Cockpit
SDCockpit.Description:
The SD Cockpit provides another viewpoint, as well
 the ability to have independent systems from the main
 core. They are automatically connected to the main
 Ship Core when placed.
 
 To cycle through cockpits, you can use the Left and Right
 Arrow Keys.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

BOBBYAIModule.name: BOBBY AI Module
BOBBYAIModule.Description:
The BOBBY AI Module is a capable of providing basic
 and rudimentary automation and functions. Useful for
 building automated turrets, amongst a few other
 applications.
 
 It can be configured by opening up your Menu (Inventory,
 Weapons, Shop, Navigation), and looking for the AI Config
 button on the bottom right.
 
 Press $ACTIVATE to Activate/Deactivate.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP
BOBBYAIModule.FullName: Dr.Plex's BOBBY Artificial Ship Control Unit

PowersupplyBeamComputer.name: Powersupply Beam-Computer
PowersupplyBeamComputer.Description:
A controller for beams transferring 
 the ship's power to another structure
 
 This beam cannot be stopped by shields,
 and can target any block of the other ship.

PowerdrainBeamComputer.name: Powerdrain Beam-Computer
PowerdrainBeamComputer.Description:
A controller for beams transferring 
 anothers structure's power to your ship.
 
 This beam cannot be stopped by shields,
 but can only drain power if power modules
 of any kind are targeted.

FactoryInput.name: FactoryInput
FactoryInput.Description:
The FactoryInput can be connected to other Factory
 Element blocks (Particle Press, Schemadyne Advanced,
 etc.) to allow for the production of certain blocks
 depending on the recipe.
 
 Linking Factories can be done by selecting one block with
 C, and then pressing V on the other factory block. Then 
 unselecting and selecting the other, and connecting the
 other. Thus creating a bi-directional link. Example in 5
 steps:
 
 1. FactoryInput (Press C to Select)
 2. Schemadyne Advanced (Press V to Connect)
 3. FactoryInput (Press C to Unselect)
 4. Schemadyne Advanced (Press C to Select)
 5. FactoryInput (Press V to Connect)
 
 Remember this all done while looking at the specific
 blocks and then performing the steps.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

FactoryInputEnhancer.name: FactoryInputEnhancer
FactoryInputEnhancer.Description:
The FactoryInputEnhancer is capable of doubling the
 production cycle of whatever Factory Element Block
 (Particle Press, SchemaDyne Advanced, etc.) it is
 connected to. To connect it, simply select the Factory
 Block in question, and then look at the
 FactoryInputEnhancer and pressing V. Or select the
 Factory Block first, then just place the Enhancers
 
 A production cycle is run every five seconds. And this
 Enhancer basically adds another cycle within that five 
 seconds. Note that, this does not mean you are getting
 more out of your materials. Merely just more per five
 seconds. You can place as many Enhancers as you'd
 like. Just remember that if you have too many, once you
 don't have enough materials to run a cycle, nothing will
 happen. Even if you have enough for the basic recipe.
 To better explain this here is an example:
 
 Particle Press Recipe
 Yhole x20 --> YHOLE NUCLEUS x1
 
 Without FactoryInputEnhancer:
 Five Seconds = Yhole x20 --> YHOLE NUCLEUS x1
 
 With Five FactoryInputEnhancers Connected:
 Five Seconds = Yhole x100 ---> YHOLE NUCLEUS x10
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

Ah yes, this "Landing" unit.. I'm not even sure I
 would put my name on this but this is DOCTOR Plex's
 GRAVILOCK Landing Unit. As long as you have enough
 of these grouped together you can easily affix any
 ship to it and lock it in place.
 
 ----------------------------------------------------
 END TRANSMISSION: MX-UV009b.1-x24.01006 DR.Plex ::
 
 Press $ACTIVATE to activate

PlexLifter.name: PlexLifter
PlexLifter.Description:
The PlexLifter can be used to create elevators and lifts
 within large stations or ships where needed. The are
 especially useful when combined with the Gravity Unit.
 Similar to PlexDoors, having them adjacent to one another
 allows for larger/longer lifts.
 
 Press $ACTIVATE to Activate/Deactivate.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

PlexUndeathinator.name: PlexUndeathinator
PlexUndeathinator.Description:
The PlexUndeathinator can be used to set a new spawn
 point should one die. To do this, simply press $ACTIVATE
 while looking at one. They can be found at shops, or
 placed on your own Space Stations or bases. They were
 not meant for ships, so use at your own risk there.
 
 -Structural Stats-
 $ARMOUR% Armour
 $HP HP

PlexRecycler.name: PlexRecycler
PlexRecycler.Description:
NOW THIS! THIS is DOCTOR Plex's finest creation!
 Yes! Yes!! DOCTOR Plex's Molecule Reporpuser will
 take any object you stick into it and almost
 instantly TRAAAAANSFORM IT ........ into ....... 
 
 A CORE!
 
 Eventually I plan to perfect the science of this
 device but until then this is all it does.
 
 ----------------------------------------------------
 END TRANSMISSION: MX-UV009b.1-x24.02000 DR.Plex ::
 
 Press $ACTIVATE to activate
 
 P.S. Dr. Plex says you're a dirty filthy cheater if
 you use this for any reason other than making
 toast!
